d logs without raising an exception, (2) the skipped-entry counter reports 3, and (3) no partial/corrupted data is included in the output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Error handling in parser is unit-testable; integration needed only if error handling is delegated to stream/pipeline layer.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Throughput under sustained load cannot be tested at unit level. A unit test with 10K in-memory objects would not expose real failure modes: file I/O overhead, buffering bottlenecks, memory pressure, garbage collection pauses, or scheduler latency. The minimum is an integration test with a realistic data source (file, stream, or rate-limited producer) sustaining 10K entries/sec, measuring actual throughput and latency behavior.","test_description":"Generate a file with 100,000 pre-formatted log entries. Feed them to the tool at a sustained 10K entries/sec rate using a timer-driven producer. Measure: (1) total entries processed, (2) count of dropped or skipped entries, (3) latency per 1K-entry batch. Verify input count equals output count plus skipped count, and per-batch latency remains stable (does not grow unboundedly).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Real I/O and throughput behavior is essential to expose buffering, memory, or processing bottlenecks; in-memory unit tests would pass even if real load fails.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.14,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13630,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13630},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier